Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and named entity recognition, which falls under this sub-category. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper uses deep learning techniques for NER. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible sub-category as the paper uses LSTM layers and CRF inference layer in the deep learning model. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible sub-category as the paper uses an entity linking module to integrate the system with Wikipedia. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible sub-category as the paper uses a neural network for NER.
